TWO-FLUID 2D HYDROSTATIC TEST WITH MIXED CELLS
----------------------------------------------

Two inviscid fluids at rest in a [-5,5]^2 domain subject to gravity; lighter
fluid on top. Fluid should remain at rest, with a linear pressure field.

With g=(0,-1,0): rho2 = 2, p = -2*y + c, in y < 1/2;
                 rho1 = 1, p = -y - 0.5 + c, in y > 1/2.

Fluid interface placed at cell midpoint.

Variations use rotated meshes (and rotated g)

&OUTPUTS
  output_t  = 0.0, 2.0
  output_dt = 2.0
/

&MESH
  mesh_file = 'mesh2.gen'
/

&PHYSICS
  flow = .true.
  body_force_density = 0.0, -1.0, 0.0
/

&FLOW
  inviscid = .true.
  courant_number = 0.5
/

&FLOW_PRESSURE_SOLVER
  rel_tol = 0.0
  abs_tol = 1.0e-12
  max_ds_iter = 50
  max_amg_iter = 25
  krylov_method = 'cg'
/

&NUMERICS
  dt_constant = 0.125
/

# FREE SLIP BC ALL AROUND
&FLOW_BC
  name = 'all sides'
  face_set_ids = 1, 2, 3, 4, 5
  type = 'free-slip'
/

# FREE SLIP BC ALL AROUND

Lower half
&BODY
  surface_name = 'plane'
  axis = 'y'
  translation_pt = 0.0, 0.5, 0.0
  material_number = 2
  velocity = 3*0.0
  temperature = 0.0
/

&INTERFACES
  vof_method = 'divide'
/

upper half
&BODY
  surface_name = 'background'
  material_number = 1
  velocity = 3*0.0
  temperature = 0.0
/

&MATERIAL
  material_name    = 'water'
  material_number  = 1
  density          = 1.0  ! not void
  material_feature = 'background'
/

&PHASE
  name = 'water'
  property_name(1) = 'density',       property_constant(1) = 2.0
  property_name(2) = 'specific heat', property_constant(2) = 1.0
/

&MATERIAL_SYSTEM
  name = 'water'
  phases = 'water'
/

&MATERIAL
  material_name    = 'oil'
  material_number  = 2
  density          = 1.0  ! not void
/

&PHASE
  name = 'oil'
  property_name(1) = 'density',       property_constant(1) = 1.0
  property_name(2) = 'specific heat', property_constant(2) = 1.0
/

&MATERIAL_SYSTEM
  name = 'oil'
  phases = 'oil'
/
